%% Definition of Done — Universal Done Gate flow
%% Read in concert with LEDGERS/DEFINITION_OF_DONE.md §4 + §5.
%% Any "no" in this flow means the work is not yet done — even if the code changed.

flowchart TD
  Start([Meaningful change made]) --> Source{Correct source<br/>of truth changed?}
  Source -->|No| FixSource[Edit canonical source<br/>not generated surface]
  FixSource --> Source
  Source -->|Yes| Guard{Guardrails &<br/>source-of-truth<br/>rules checked?}

  Guard -->|No| ApplyGuard[Re-check Guardrails.html /<br/>comeketo-inbox skill /<br/>Global §4 rules]
  ApplyGuard --> Guard
  Guard -->|Yes| Verify{Verification run<br/>or honestly explained?}

  Verify -->|No| Explain[Run a check OR record<br/>'not verified because…'<br/>in Open Problems]
  Explain --> Verify
  Verify -->|Yes| Memory{Affected ledgers / maps /<br/>Box notes updated?}

  Memory -->|No| UpdateLedger[Update relevant ledger<br/>per §6 Update Matrix]
  UpdateLedger --> Memory
  Memory -->|Yes| Open{Open problems<br/>recorded?}

  Open -->|Yes / new found| RecordProblem[Append PROB-YYYY-MM-DD-###<br/>to Open Problems Ledger]
  RecordProblem --> Handoff
  Open -->|None / already logged| Handoff{Handoff context<br/>left in repo?}

  Handoff -->|No| AddHandoff[Communications Ledger entry<br/>or Temporal Continuity update<br/>or per-Box audit marker]
  AddHandoff --> Handoff
  Handoff -->|Yes| Commit{Committed?<br/>Push status clear?}

  Commit -->|No| DoCommit[Commit. Decide push vs<br/>local-only with Jake.]
  DoCommit --> Commit
  Commit -->|Yes| Done([DONE])

  classDef gate fill:#fff7d6,stroke:#b08a00,stroke-width:1px;
  classDef fix fill:#ffe9e9,stroke:#a33,stroke-width:1px;
  classDef terminal fill:#dcffd6,stroke:#2a8a2a,stroke-width:2px;

  class Source,Guard,Verify,Memory,Open,Handoff,Commit gate;
  class FixSource,ApplyGuard,Explain,UpdateLedger,RecordProblem,AddHandoff,DoCommit fix;
  class Start,Done terminal;
